Waffle. Sandwiches. When done right, these are two things that really hit the spot. If you haven't tried Bruxie, you should really give it a try! At least once! It's pretty much a small shack with a lot of outdoor seating. They have a TON of different kinds of waffle sandwiches on the menu, with a lot of specials you can try. Apparently their fried chicken and waffles is their best seller, but I have yet to try that. First of all, the waffles are what I'd have to say make the sandwich. Yes, each sandwich is good in that the combinations create the flavor, but what really makes the sandwiches stick are definitely because of the crunchy-on-the-outside, soft-on-the-inside waffles. They come out so fresh and warm, and it is just amazing once you bite into it. I've tried most of the things on their menu, and here's what I would recommend: - Green Eggs and Ham: oh god. this one is so delicious, I can't even describe! Maybe it's because I'm a sucker for breakfast food, but I think the combination of it all is just amazing. This sandwich combines grilled ham, tillamook cheddar, jumbo egg, mayo, and arugula pesto. Traditional ham, egg, and cheese...you can't go wrong with that! And flavoring it up with mayo and pesto just gives it a nice creamy flavor. All of the stuff on the inside is fairly soft and chewy, so the waffle sandwich creates a nice contrast, texture wise. - Turkey Club: this one's pretty good too. Yeah, a turkey club sandwich...typical, right? I don't know man, there's something about using the waffle that makes this sandwich particularly good. There's turkey, gruyere, avocado, applewood smoked bacon, sliced tomatoes, lettuce, and pesto aoili inside. I think maybe there's something to do with the avocado too... but this one is pretty delicious! - Strawberry Creme Brulee: this one's pretty good too. It has classic vanilla creme with burnt raw sugar & strawberries. Oh hey, I was just about to write that it tastes like creme brulee when I realized that that's what they were going for. So yes! Creme brulee...in a waffle sandwich! Again, soft and delicious on the inside, crunchy on the outside. It's not too sweet and it's a great way to end your meal if you like dessert! I can't wait to try some of the seasonal stuff they have on the menu. Looks quite delicious :D
