e Holiday, it was actually featured in a local newspaper!  Pulled pork with cranberry sauce & stuffing.  What??  Yes that sounds amazingly good and it even comes with a side of jus that is heavily flavored with all the familiar herbs present at holiday dinners.  There's a huge amount of tender pulled pork and it was easily the biggest sandwich out of the three and if you didn't get enough of holiday flavors, then go and get it before they stop serving it as a special! You can order any of the sandwiches as a combo with waffle fries so that is what we did.  The fries come in a little baggie and nothing too crazy about them.  It was sorta lukewarm when we got ours.  It doesn't come with a drink but if you're a fan of sodas, definitely get their old fashioned sodas.  All their sodas are sweetened with natural cane sugar.  It is sweet but it never tastes overly sweet for some reason!  Awesome. Since I don't know when I'll be back in this area, I wanted to get something sweet and went for the Liege Waffle with Caramelized Pearl Sugar.  I don't really know how to explain the Liege waffle except that it looks like a regular Belgium waffle, super buttery, denser, and crunchy.  The sugar provides the crunch factor and if the sugar is not enough, you can choose between Nutella or Strawberry for additional flavor!  I went for Nutella since I'm a sucker for it and I didn't want to be bothered while eating.  The only reason I stopped eating the waffle was cause my friend ordered a soft serve so I asked if I could scoop some to add it to my Liege Waffle.  Besides ordering the fried chicken sandwich, that was probably the best idea all day.  Ice cream + waffle + Nutella = heaven. I must find another reason to head out to Orange.  I must!
