 eat fast, but not this time...  I ate slowly to taste all the ingredients...  I savored every bite as the flavors danced on my tastebuds.  I seriously closed my eyes as I took each bite and let the flavors melt into my mouth. Seasonal Creme Brulee It has classic vanilla creme with burnt raw sugar and fresh fruit, today it was strawberries.  That thing was loaded with fresh strawberries.  I took one bite and it was over.  I surrendered.  The waffle was on point.  The creme brulee held me captive.  I thought it might be some kind of substitute for some reason--  but it really did taste like creme brulee, but in a waffle sandwich!  haha  I don't know what I was expecting, but that initial bite...  Yumm...  Strong creme brulee sweetness.  Come on, it's Creme freakin' brulee!  'Nuff said.   Seasonal Menu Item:  Strawberry Cheesecake This one was also loaded with fresh strawberries, with the waffle cooked to perfection.  It was strawberry heaven.  It was creamy and not as sweet as the creme brulee.  The cheesecake had a slight tart flavor and the strawberries beautifully accented the exquisite flavor.  So, I personally liked the cheesecake more than the brulee.   Strawberry Lemonade It was a bit tart for my taste.  I kind of prefer mine to be more sweeter like Auntie Anne's because it's loaded with sweetness and sugary goodness.  lol  That's how strong my sweet tooth is!  It was good and refreshing no less! // FOOD //  A+ * * * * *  Closing Comments  * * * * *   I will definitely come back as much as I can to try out everything else while trying to keep my waistline from bulging.  Service is fantastic.  The food?  Phenomenal.  I love trying new things and this was quite a food experience.  Mind you, I'm not a seasoned foodie or self-proclaimed critic like a lot of people are on here.  I'm just a girl in love with food.  And I can honestly say that I'm in love with Bruxies. ...I was going to put 4 stars because I'm definitely a fan and will come back any chance I get, but as I was writing this review--  I realized that I have no true complaints--  so, I decided to give 5 stars, because truly it IS as good as it gets! 'Twas a Bold Fold, indeed, my newfound friend. Believe the hype. // OVERALL //  A+
